{"ts":"2026-06-27T09:56:07.726Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"zwvp93o7","input":{"summary":"### Files Changed:\n- `backend/app/core/config.py`: Dynamically resolves the absolute path of `backend/dev.db` so the local SQLite database is reliably initialized relative to the config file path, rather than depending on the arbitrary working directory of the execution context.\n- `backend/app/db/__init__.py`: Properly exports the `Base` metadata class, database `engine`, session factory `SessionLocal`, dependency provider `get_db`, and initialization helper `init_db`.\n- `backend/app/db/init_db.py`: Implemented a clean, centralized database initialization routine to compile and create tables from all registered SQLAlchemy models.\n- `backend/app/main.py`: Refactored lifespan handler to invoke `init_db` for automatic database creation on startup.\n- `backend/app/seed.py`: Refactored seeding routine to use `init_db` instead of inline creation logic.\n\n### Summary of Implementation:\n- Established a clean database setup using **SQLAlchemy** to configure the engine and session factory (`SessionLocal`) for a local SQLite database (`backend/dev.db`).\n- Resolved pathing dynamically so local SQLite operations do not result in misplaced `.db` files.\n- Provided a `get_db` FastAPI dependency helper to handle session lifecycle events automatically inside API endpoints.\n- Isolated all metadata registrations under `backend/app/db/base.py` to ensure SQLAlchemy is fully aware of all models on startup.\n- Utilized an automated database creation routine via `init_db` on server launch and on manual database seeding.\n\n### Validation Done:\n- Successfully executed the manual seed script `backend/venv/bin/python backend/app/seed.py`, which correctly connects, verifies/creates the SQLite schemas, and inserts default operational roles and logging records cleanly.\n- Confirmed with a Python import check that all configuration modules, database layers, models, and FastAPI app scripts compile and import perfectly without any warnings or circular reference errors.\n- Verified that all UI code, the Next.js landing page, public route paths, and frontend rules are completely untouched and safe.\n\n### Limitations:\n- Implemented as a local-only MVP SQLite engine setup to comply with GFF AI AI project guardrails (no production Postgres, AWS database clusters, or external credentials required).","verified":true}}}
